From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: suckbluefrog <suckbluefrog@proton.me>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 06:05:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] lunasvg: include fixed-width integer types in public header

lunasvg.h declares APIs using std::uint8_t, std::uint32_t, and
std::size_t, but this vendored revision relies on those types arriving
through unrelated transitive includes. GCC 13 does not provide that here,
which leaves the Bitmap API undeclared and causes a cascade of errors in
lunasvg.cpp.

Include the standard headers that define the public API types directly.

Signed-off-by: suckbluefrog <suckbluefrog@proton.me>
---
 src/external/lunasvg/include/lunasvg.h | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/external/lunasvg/include/lunasvg.h b/src/external/lunasvg/include/lunasvg.h
index b48467e2..423a24ec 100644
--- a/src/external/lunasvg/include/lunasvg.h
+++ b/src/external/lunasvg/include/lunasvg.h
@@ -22,6 +22,8 @@
 #ifndef LUNASVG_H
 #define LUNASVG_H
 
+#include <cstddef>
+#include <cstdint>
 #include <memory>
 #include <string>
 
-- 
